# User Documentation

This document explains how to access and use the WordPress website deployed with the Inception project.

---

## Overview

The Inception project deploys a WordPress website secured with HTTPS.
All technical aspects (containers, database, network) are handled automatically.
This document focuses only on how to use the website as an end user.

---

## Website Access

The website is accessible via **HTTPS only**.

URL: https://nabil.42.fr

The domain name must be locally mapped to the virtual machine IP using the `/etc/hosts` file.

Example: <VM_IP_ADDRESS> nabil.42.fr


## Browser Compatibility

The website can be accessed using any modern web browser, including:
- Firefox
- Chromium
- Google Chrome
- Brave
- Safari

---

## WordPress Accounts

Two WordPress accounts are created automatically during installation:

- **Administrator account**
  - Full access to the WordPress dashboard
  - Can manage users, content, and settings

- **Author account**
  - Can create and manage posts only

Credentials are **not stored in the repository** and are injected securely using Docker secrets during installation.

---

## WordPress Dashboard Access

To access the WordPress administration interface, go to: https://nabil.42.fr/wp-admin


You will be redirected to the login page if not authenticated.

---

## Start and Stop the Website

### Start and Stop the website
```bash

make up
